Previous discussions are based on MDCG is placed on a semi-infinite substrate, which is reasonable for applications in fibers, solar cells and so on. But in most other cases, an independent ALT device is highly desired, where the diffraction lights should transmit out the substrate. However, the large diffraction angle in grating-based ALT devices may result in a total internal reflection at the interface between substrate and air for diffraction lights. To fully understand this phenomenon, we firstly calculate the critical angle in our case which is θc=arcsin(nl2nl1)=arcsin(11.59)≈43.3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
